lyrics_snippet: I stay out too late, got nothing in my brain, that's what people say, I'm dancing on my own
Clap along if you feel like a room without a roof, because I'm happy
I'm walking on sunshine and don't it feel good
You can dance, you can jive, having the time of your life
I got that sunshine in my pocket, got that good soul in my feet
Never mind I'll find someone like you, I wish nothing but the best for you
Oh won't you stay with me, cause you're all I need
Don't you know I'm no good for you, I've learned to lose you can't afford to
When you try your best but you don't succeed, tears stream down your face
Now the day bleeds into nightfall and you're not here to get me through it all
Those who died are justified for wearing the badge they're the chosen whites
Everything you say to me takes me one step closer to the edge and I'm about to break
I am whatever you say I am, if I wasn't then why would I say I am
Bow down before the one you serve, you're going to get what you deserve
Master of puppets I'm pulling your strings, twisting your mind and smashing your dreams
I waited til I saw the sun, don't know why I didn't come
When your legs don't work like they used to before, I will be loving you til we're seventy
Don't worry about a thing, cause every little thing gonna be alright
Here comes the sun and I say it's alright, little darling it's been a long cold lonely winter
Gravity is working against me, and gravity wants to bring me down
